abraflexi-matcher (1.3.5) experimental; urgency=medium

  * Add/update manpages for all 13 installed commands (previously only
    5 existed, one of them still the unfilled mdoc(7) template and
    another empty); moved them into debian/ alongside the other
    packaging files and updated debian/manpages accordingly. Removed
    the obsolete MATCHER_PULL_BANK mentions and documented
    MATCHER_LOCALIZE, buc/smerKod/IBAN matching and duplicate_buc
    reporting where relevant.
  * README/README.cs.md: link each command name to its manpage, use
    proper fenced code blocks for the apt install and configuration
    examples (the previous indented blocks did not render as code on
    GitHub), and remove the stale /etc/abraflexi/client.json and
    matcher.json references - configuration has been environment
    variable/.env-based for a while and those files are no longer read.
  * Drop the leftover MATCHER_PULL_BANK line from example.env.

 -- Vítězslav Dvořák <info@vitexsoftware.cz>  Fri, 17 Jul 2026 15:00:00 +0200

abraflexi-matcher (1.3.4) experimental; urgency=medium

  * Normalize IBAN by stripping whitespace before matching/storing it
    (findInvoiceCandidatesByAccountNo, ibanToAddress, isKnownIbanForAddress,
    assignBankAccountToAddress, savePayerAccount): confirmed against real
    production data on flexibee.freetel.cz that bank-imported payment
    records commonly carry IBAN formatted with spaces (e.g. "CZ69 0300
    0000 0002 7998 2653"), while invoices are entered without them, so an
    exact-string IBAN filter silently failed to match otherwise-identical
    accounts.

 -- Vítězslav Dvořák <info@vitexsoftware.cz>  Fri, 17 Jul 2026 14:15:00 +0200

abraflexi-matcher (1.3.3) experimental; urgency=medium

  * Fix bank-code (smerKod) comparisons in the accountno matcher
    (filterByMatchingBankCode, bucToAddress, findInvoiceCandidatesByAccountNo,
    assignBankAccountToAddress): smerKod is a relation field, so AbraFlexi
    always returns it as an AbraFlexi\Relation object, never null/empty,
    even when unset - PHP's empty()/null checks on that object are always
    false regardless of the underlying value, so a payment with no bank
    code silently failed to match ANY candidate (including exact buc
    matches) and duplicate buc/company records went undetected instead of
    being reported. All smerKod values are now normalized to plain strings
    before comparison. Found and fixed via a live test scenario on
    vyvojar.brevnov.czf (company 21) exercising domestic buc+smerKod
    match, IBAN match, bank-code mismatch, and duplicate-buc reporting.

 -- Vítězslav Dvořák <info@vitexsoftware.cz>  Fri, 17 Jul 2026 13:45:00 +0200

abraflexi-matcher (1.3.2) experimental; urgency=medium

  * Add duplicate_buc metric to varsym/specsym/accountno matcher reports,
    listing bank account numbers registered to more than one address in
    AbraFlexi (data inconsistency previously only visible as a log
    'event' with no reporting) together with the conflicting
    companies (kod/nazev) and the payment document(s) being processed
    when the ambiguity was hit, so it can be resolved without further
    manual lookup.
  * Match bank account number together with bank code (smerKod) in the
    accountno matcher, isKnownBankAccountForAddress() and bucToAddress():
    the account number alone is not unique across banks, so payments
    could previously be matched to an invoice/payer whose buc happens to
    coincide with a different bank's account. Records with no smerKod on
    file are still matched by buc alone, to stay compatible with existing
    incomplete data.
  * Support matching foreign payments by IBAN in the accountno matcher:
    such payments carry no account number/bank code (buc/smerKod) at all,
    only an IBAN, so they were previously always skipped entirely and
    reported as unmatched. savePayerAccount()/assignBankAccountToAddress()
    now also record/recognise a payer's IBAN.
  * Remove the MATCHER_PULL_BANK option and its stahnoutVypisyOnline() call
    from all matcher entrypoints (abraflexi-match-varsym/specsym/accountno,
    abraflexi-matcher-out, abraflexi-matcher/abraflexi-matcher-in,
    abraflexi-matcher-new2old, abraflexi-match-cash): matchers now assume
    the bank statements already contain every record to process and never
    pull them inline. Statement download stays available as a separate
    step via abraflexi-pull-bank.
  * Translate remaining Czech source strings in ParovacFaktur.php (e.g.
    "Přeplatek - DOBROPIS: ...") to English so the gettext source language
    is uniform; the previous Czech wording is preserved as the cs_CZ
    translation. Removed the now-orphaned "pull account statements"
    catalog entry left over from the MATCHER_PULL_BANK removal.
  * Add sk_SK and en_US gettext catalogs (i18n/sk_SK, i18n/en_US) alongside
    the existing cs_CZ one.
  * multiflexi/*.app.json: expose MATCHER_LOCALIZE (the env var actually
    read by the matcher scripts) as a proper "set" option with the
    available languages (en_US/cs_CZ/sk_SK, en_US default) instead of the
    unused/mismatched "LANG" field.

 -- Vítězslav Dvořák <info@vitexsoftware.cz>  Fri, 17 Jul 2026 00:45:00 +0200

abraflexi-matcher (1.3.1) experimental; urgency=medium

  * Fix uncaught AbraFlexi\Exception in ParovacFaktur::assignBankAccountToAddress()
    crashing the whole matcher batch (exit 255, no report written) whenever a
    payer's bank account lacks a bank code/IBAN pair required by AbraFlexi.
    Affects all three split matchers (varsym/specsym/accountno) since they
    share the same settleInvoice()/savePayerAccount() code path. (#72)

